        public static boolean currentProgram(java.lang.String path,
                                     SeparateChainingHashST<java.lang.String,Airport> airportST,
                                     SeparateChainingHashST<java.lang.String,Airline> airlineST,
                                     RedBlackBST<java.lang.Integer,Airplane> airplaneST,
                                     RedBlackBST<Date,Flight> flightST)
        File holding the previous program opened so changes like additions, editions and removals of any info is stored on it aswell as the flights occurred
        Parameters:
        path - path to the file
        airportST - will populate this ST with the airports
        airlineST - will populate this ST with the airlines
        airplaneST - will populate this ST with the airplanes
        flightST - will populate this ST with the flights
        Returns:
        returns false if the file is empty and true if the read was successful and there's data to begin the program
